    "department": "Enterprise",
    "description": "Position Overview\n\nWe are seeking an Engineer II to join our cloud-based Network Management System (NMS) development team. This entry-level position is perfect for recent graduates or early-career engineers who want to build expertise in network management software while working on cutting-edge cloud platforms that manage enterprise network infrastructure including switches, routers, and WiFi access points.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n - Feature Development: Implement well-defined features for network device monitoring and management interfaces under senior engineer guidance\n\n - UI Component Development: Build responsive web components for network dashboards, device status displays, and configuration forms\n\n - API Integration: Integrate frontend components with existing backend APIs for device data retrieval and configuration\n\n - Bug Fixes: Identify, troubleshoot, and resolve software defects in network management applications\n\n - Testing: Write unit tests and perform integration testing for network management features\n\n - Documentation: Create and maintain technical documentation for implemented features\n\n - Code Reviews: Participate in code review processes and learn from senior team members\n\n - Learning \u0026 Development: Actively learn networking fundamentals, cloud technologies, and company-specific domain knowledge\n\n - Quality Assurance: Support QA processes by testing network device integrations and user workflows\n\n - Minor Enhancements: Implement small improvements to existing network monitoring and configuration tools\n\nTechnical Requirements\n\n - Frontend Basics: Foundational knowledge of HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, and one modern framework (React.js preferred)\n\n - Backend Fundamentals: Basic understanding of RESTful APIs, JSON, and server-side programming (Node.js, Python, or Java)\n\n - Database Basics: Understanding of SQL databases and basic query operations\n\n - Version Control: Proficiency with Git for collaborative development\n\n - Development Tools: Familiarity with modern IDEs, debugging tools, and basic command-line operations\n\n - Web Technologies: Understanding of HTTP protocols, web security basics, and responsive design\n\n - Learning Aptitude: Strong willingness to learn networking concepts, cloud platforms, and domain-specific technologies\n\nNetworking Knowledge (Training Provided)\n\n - Basic understanding of TCP/IP and networking fundamentals\n\n - Curiosity about network devices and infrastructure management\n\n - Interest in learning about network protocols, device configuration, and monitoring systems\n\n - No prior network management experience required - comprehensive training provided\n\nQualifications\n\n - Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or related technical field\n\n - 2-4 years of software development experience (internships and projects count)\n\n - Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail\n\n - Good communication skills and ability to work collaboratively\n\n - Eagerness to learn and adapt to new technologies\n\n - Basic understanding of software development lifecycle\n\nGrowth Opportunities\n\n - Comprehensive onboarding program covering networking fundamentals and NMS concepts\n\n - Mentorship from senior engineers with networking and cloud expertise\n\n - Hands-on training with network devices and management protocols\n\n - Career development path toward network software specialization\n\nCompany Statement/Values:  \n\nAt NETGEAR, we are on a mission to unleash the full potential of connectivity with intelligent solutions that delight and protect. We turn ideas into innovative networking products that connect people, power businesses, and advance the way we live.  \n\nWe're a performance-driven, talented and connected team that's committed to delivering world-class products for our customers. As a company, we value our employees as the most essential building blocks of our success. And as teammates, we commit to taking our work to the Next Gear by living our values: we Dare to Transform the future, Connect and Delight our customers, Communicate Courageously with each other and collaborate to Win It Together. You’ll find our values woven through our processes, present in our decisions, and celebrated throughout our culture. \n\nWe strive to attract top talent and create a great workplace where people feel engaged, inspired, challenged, proud and respected. If you are creative, forward-thinking, passionate about technology and are looking for a rewarding career to make an impact, then you've got what it takes to succeed at NETGEAR. Join our network and help us shape the future of connectivity. \n\nNETGEAR hires based on merit. All qualified applicants will receive equal consideration for employment. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.",
